-- Greece to auction 1 bln eur of 6-month T-bills on April 8
-- 
-- Fri Apr 04, 2014 05:50AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, April 4 (Reuters) - Greece will auction 1 billion euros ($1.37 billion) of six-month treasury bills on April 8 to refinance a maturing issue, the country's debt management agency PDMA said on Friday.

The settlement date will be April 11. Only primary dealers will be allowed to participate and no commission will be paid.